# GGS2 Development Standards

# Project Context
You are developing the GGS2 Investigator Management Portal for พ.ต.ท.กฤษกร (กก.สส.2 บก.สส.ภ.8). The system is designed for high-security, high-reliability police operations.

# Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js (App Router)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Components: Shadcn/UI (Radix UI)
- Backend: Supabase (Auth, Postgres, RLS)
- Icons: Lucide React

# Coding Rules
- Modular Structure: Break components into reusable parts.
- Type Safety: Use strict TypeScript interfaces for all data structures (Officer, Task).
- Clean UI: Use the official police-themed color palette (#800000 Maroon, #ffd700 Gold).
- Comments: Explain complex logic, especially scoring algorithms.

# Security
- Never log sensitive PII (ID cards, suspect names) to the console.
- Always check for user authentication before rendering sensitive officer portfolios.
- Ensure Row Level Security (RLS) is considered when designing database functions.
